   email
   https://litmus.com/blog/uncovering-the-metrics-behind-an-award-winning-
   email#comments Thu, 10 Mar 2016 15:28:18 +0000 Lauren Smith Inspiration
   Tips & Resources Uncategorized analytics click rate eec award
   engagement metrics open rate performance twitter feed
   https://litmus.com/blog/?p=11887 <p>While opens and clicks are a great
   way to measure overall engagement, they don't paint the whole picture
   of a campaign's performance. Our award-winning campaign didn't have
   high opens or clicks, but it did accomplish its goal of creating
   awareness and generating buzz around The Email Design Conference. </p>
   <p>The post <a rel="nofollow"
   href="https://litmus.com/blog/uncovering-the-metrics-behind-an-award-wi
   nning-email">Uncovering the Metrics Behind an Award-Winning Email</a>
   appeared first on <a rel="nofollow"
   href="https://litmus.com/blog">Litmus Blog</a>.</p> <p>Every
   interaction with your subscribers counts. Send emails that your
   subscribers want, that are relevant to their needs and interests, that
   excite them, and (most importantly!) that make them want to take
   action. </p> <p>Campaigns that accomplish all the above not only win
   the hearts and minds of your customers, they&#8217;re a win for your
   business. And we&#8217;re particularly proud of one campaign in
   particular that also won an award: the <a
   href="https://emailexperience.org/events/dma-email-experience-councils-
   email-marketing-awards/2016-eec-award-winners/">2016 EEC Email
   Marketing Program Award</a> for úBest or Most Innovative Integration
   with Another Channel.ù</p> <p>That campaign was our save the date email
   for TEDC15 (The Email Design Conference).</p> <p>What surprised us?
   This campaign wasnôt a success because it had the most opens or clicks.
   In fact, it had much lower open and click rates compared to our other
   emails. </p> <p>However, opens and clicks wasnôt our goal. The main
   call-to-action in the campaign asked our readers to tweetîand, boy, did
   we get a lot of tweets! It excelled at its stated goals of driving
   awareness and creating buzz around the conference, and weôre humbled and
   grateful to have won an award in recognition of those efforts! </p>
   <h2>A look at the campaign</h2> <h3>The goals</h3> <p>After <a
   href="https://litmus.com/blog/how-to-code-html5-video-background-in-ema
   il?utm_campaign=inspiration_eecaward&#038;utm_source=litmusblog&#038;ut
   m_medium=blog">embedding a video background</a> into TEDC14ôs úsave the
   date,ù we had set high expectations with the community for a follow-up
   in 2015. As such, the primary goal of the campaign was to surprise,
   delight, and inspire our audience with a creative use of email,
   preferably leveraging a technique that is rarely seen or thought to be
   unsupported in email. </p> <p>By utilizing innovative techniques in
   event-related emails, we wanted to demonstrate thought leadership and
   prove to our subscribers that we have the expertise and skills to teach
   others at TEDC. Additional goals were to raise awareness and excitement
   about the event, drive social mentions, and create anticipation for
   future ticket sales. </p> <h3>The email</h3> <p>After many
   brainstorming sessions, we opted to announce dates and generate
   excitement for TEDC15 by embedding an <a
   href="https://litmus.com/blog/how-to-code-a-live-dynamic-twitter-feed-i
   n-html-email?utm_campaign=inspiration_eecaward&#038;utm_source=litmusbl
   og&#038;utm_medium=blog">innovative live Twitter feed</a> inside an
   email. </p> <figure id="post-10014 media-10014" class="aligncenter
   nudged" style="margin-right: 0;"><a
   href="http://pages.litmus.com/lp/TEDC15-launch-email"
   target="_blank"><img
   src="https://d31v04zdn5vmni.cloudfront.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016
   /03/tedc15-email-002.png" alt="tedc15-email" /></a></figure> <p><em>You
   can view the <a
   href="http://pages.litmus.com/lp/TEDC15-launch-email">full email in
   your browser</a>, or check out the <a
   href="https://litmus.com/pub/c039b69/screenshots">Litmus test
   results</a> to see how it displayed in 40+ email clients.</em> </p>
   <p>úSave the dateù emails were sent to Litmus subscribers and past
   attendees. Each contained a live dynamic Twitter feed featuring tweets
   using the #TEDC15 hashtag. As recipients opened the email, live tweets
   appeared within the email. Subscribers tweeted using the hashtag, then
   returned to the email to see their own message appear live in the
   stream <em>inside</em> the email.</p> <h2>Measuring success: What
   metrics matter?</h2> <p>The campaign garnered widespread attention,
   resulting in 5,000 new visitors to the Litmus website, 1,000 new
   prospects, and 750 tweets containing the event hashtagîall within 24
   hours. </p> <p>To date, itôs garnered nearly 1,260 forwards and 350
   prints. More than 60% of the people that opened the email spent 18 or
   more seconds reading the message, the highest duration of engagement of
   any email weôve ever sent. </p> <p>When we launched ticket sales a few
   weeks later, early bird tickets sold out in 10 minutes for the Boston
   event and 48 hours for the London event.</p> <p>Despite being sent
   nearly a year ago, the campaign continues to drive additional email and
   social engagement as users re-visit the email and contribute to the
   Twitter stream. </p> <p>The goal of this campaign went beyond opens and
   clicks to draw the email community together and create awareness for
   the event. Between hundreds of tweets, dozens of forwards and prints,
   and early bird tickets selling in minutes, it exceeded every
   expectation.</p> <h2>Whatôs your most successful campaign? </h2> <p>Many
   marketers focus on open and click rates. While those metrics can be a
   great way to measure overall engagement, they donôt paint the whole
   picture of a campaignôs performance, especially when different emails
   have different goals. </p> <p>What has been your most successful
   campaign? How did you measure its success? </p> <p><a
   href="https://litmus.com/community/discussions/4925-email-campaign-succ
   ess-metrics?utm_campaign=inspiration_eecaward&#038;utm_source=litmusblo
   g&#038;utm_medium=blog">Share it with us in Community í </a> </p>
   <h2>Want to see what other email goodies we have up our sleeve?</h2>
   <p>Tickets for TEDC16 are launching soon. And, we have something extra
   special in store (hopefully weôll be writing about it this time again
   next year!)! Subscribe to get our newsletterîand TEDC newsîdelivered
   straight to your inbox.<br /> <iframe style="border: 0;"
   src="https://litmus.com/l/31032/2014-02-17/hsgc" height="200"
   width="100%" frameborder="0"></iframe></p> <p>The post <a
   rel="nofollow"
   href="https://litmus.com/blog/uncovering-the-metrics-behind-an-award-wi
   nning-email">Uncovering the Metrics Behind an Award-Winning Email</a>
   appeared first on <a rel="nofollow"
   href="https://litmus.com/blog">Litmus Blog</a>.</p>
